  "title": "Engineer cum Architectural Drafter",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><u><strong>Drafter Scope of works : -</strong></u></li><li>Prepare detailed drawings using Autocad, SketchUp based on Architectural and structural drawings.</li><li>Prepare As-built drawings to reflect construction changes.</li><li>Support site team with drawing clarifications and modifications during installation stages.</li><li>To maintain , update and compile all drawing files as required.</li><li>Co-ordinate with Project managers to ensure drawing accuracy and compliance with project specifications.</li><li><u><strong>Site Engineering & Supervision :-</strong></u></li><li>Implement of documents for submission : -</li><li>RA (Risk Assessment)</li><li>Method of statement</li><li>Working permit</li><li>Materials submission</li><li>Supervise daily construction activities to ensure work is carried out as per approved drawings & specifications.</li><li>Co-ordinate with contractors, site workers to maintain smooth workflow.</li><li>Monitor site progress, highlight any deviations or technical issues.</li><li>Conduct site measurements and verify materials quantities as per drawings.</li><li>Ensure compliance with safety regulations and quanlity standards at site.</li><li>Attend site meetings</li><li>Maintain communication between Office based team and Site Personnel</li></ul><p><u><strong>Required Skilled or Qualifications :-</strong></u></p><ul><li>Dipolma or Bachelor's degree in Architectural , Civil Engineering , or related filed</li><li>Proficiency in Autocad, Revit , Sketchup , MS Office , Words.</li><li>Strong understanding of Architectural drawings, Construction Practices and detailing.</li></ul><p>Ability to manage site activities & co-ordinate multiple teams.</p><p><u><strong>Experience : -</strong></u></p><p>3-5 years of experience in Architectural drafting and site supervision.</p><p><u><strong>Work Environment : -</strong></u></p><ul><li>Combination of office based drafting work and on-site supervision.</li></ul>",
